Introduction

We have been asked to help Budweiser identify which cities should host events for breweries.

The provided datasets contain two lists of 2410 US craft beers across 558 US breweries consisting of the style of beer, ABV (Alcohol by Volume), IBU (International Bitterness Units), and the brewery’s city and state.

Chart 1 quantifies the varying number of breweries in each state from 1 (DC, ND, SD, WV) to 47 (CO).

Question 7

Chart 9 reflects an apparent positive relationship between IBU and ABV values.

The black dotted line is the mean ABV at that value of IBU. The yellow shading is the standard deviation. While there is positive correlation between the ABV and IBU with a maximum ABV value peaking out around 10%, there are two outliers that warrant further examination for inclusion or exclusion depending on additional questions of interest.

Chart 9: Alcohol By Volume vs International Bitterness Units of beer

Conclusion

Our initial findings yielded that Colorado has the most breweries at 47 (8.42%) of the total 558 in the US whereas Washington DC, North Dakota, South Dakota, and West Virginia each have one. Of the 2410 beers in the provided dataset, there were 62 with missing ABV values and 1005 with missing IBU values but still showed an overall positive relationship between the two variables. Four of the states east of the Mississippi River have the highest median ABV above 6%, i.e. Washington DC, Kentucky, Michigan, West Virginia with only Colorado and New Mexico and Colorado west of the River above 6%. The latter with the maximum ABV at 12.8% among the 50% of the beers that have an ABV between 5% and 6.7%. Oregon holds the record for maximum IBU at 138.

While the analysis of this dataset yielded interesting insights about the 558 breweries’ 2410 beers, we feel it fails to accurately answer the question of where the events should be hosted. It would be beneficial to collect and merge additional variables about the number of personnel per breweries and their job functions, number of retail alcohol establishments, city and state population, nearest major airports, etc.to better recommend the event locations fo maximum attendance and exposure.
